mondo_label: mitochondrial complex v (atp synthase) deficiency nuclear type 4
original_label: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 4

definition: An acquired metabolic disease that is characterized by the endogenous production of ethanol produced through endogenous fermentation by fungi or bacteria in the gastrointestinal system, oral cavity, or urinary system and typically presents with the signs of alcohol intoxication.
An acquired metabolic disease that is characterized by ethanol fermentation in the bladder and the absence of alcoholic intoxication.
A thyroid gland carcinoma composed of groups of carcinoma cells with thymic epithelial differentiation.
A thyroid gland carcinoma that is characterized by the presence of cribriform, trabecular, follicular, papillary, and solid growth patterns and squamoid morulae formation.

mondo_label: thyroid gland mixed medullary and follicular cell-derived carcinoma
original_label: thyroid gland mixed medullary and follicular cell-derived carcinoma
definition: A thyroid gland carcinoma containing a medullary carcinoma component that is immunohistochemically positive for calcitonin, and follicular cell-derived carcinoma component that is immunohistochemically positive for thyroglobulin.
A thyroid gland carcinoma that is characterized by the presence of clusters of malignant epithelial cells associated with abundant extracellular mucin deposition.
A pulmonary fibrosis that is characterized by scarring of the lung characterized by  stiffness in the lungs and makes it difficult to breathe.
